Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.32,0:21:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}也就几百岁或上千岁{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}just a few hundred years old or a thousand years old.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.78,0:21:31.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那可能是关键的环节{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}That could be the critical link.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.12,0:21:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们看到的这个要比我们所看到的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We're seeing this one when it's much younger...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.29,0:21:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}多数脉冲星年轻得多{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}than most pulsars that we see.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.04,0:21:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙间有某些不同寻常的星球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Some unusual stars exist in the cosmos...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.51,0:21:47.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但太空中也同样有怪异的小不点存在{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but there is equally odd small stuff in space.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.34,0:21:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}最近 科学家已经解开了整个宇宙间{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And recently, scientists have solved the mystery...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.43,0:21:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}最难以捉摸的东西之一的谜团{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}surrounding one of the most elusive things in the entire universe...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.31,0:22:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}每时每刻都在穿越我们的幽灵粒子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}a ghostly particle that passes through us every second of every day.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.82,0:22:10.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙号称拥有无穷无尽的...{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The universe lays claim to infinite numbers...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.78,0:22:12.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}异常行星和恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of abnormal planets and stars.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.62,0:22:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}与此同时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}At the same time...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.00,0:22:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太空中同样拥有怪异的小不点{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there are equally strange small things in space.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.21,0:22:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}人类以及大部分宇宙{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Human beings and most of the universe...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.88,0:22:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是由普通物质构成的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}are made up of normal matter...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.59,0:22:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其中主要包括了四种基本粒子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which primarily consists of four fundamental particles.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.97,0:22:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其中之一就是幽灵般的粒子 叫做中微子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}One is a ghost-like particle called a neutrino.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.52,0:22:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}中微子 我会认为是...{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Neutrinos would be my vote...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.06,0:22:43.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙间最奇异的普通物质{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}for some of the weirdest normal matter in the universe.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.32,0:22:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就在此时 每秒钟{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}At this very moment, every second...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.11,0:22:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有50万亿个中微子来自太阳{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there are 50 trillion neutrinos actually coming from the Sun...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.24,0:22:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}穿过我的身体{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that are passing through my body...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.95,0:22:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}还有中微子来自其它恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and there are other neutrinos from other stars...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.74,0:22:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}从四面八方奔向地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}coming in different directions right through the Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.29,0:23:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这些东西 数以万亿计 一刻不停涌入我体内{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}These things, by the trillions, are pouring into me every second...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.87,0:23:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但是我们却毫无觉察{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but we're completely unaware of them.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.71,0:23:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们根本不会与我们相互作用{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They don't really interact with us at all.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.96,0:23:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有一种小粒子叫做中微子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}There's a funny little particle called a neutrino...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.22,0:23:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是意大利语中的"小中性粒子"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Italian for "little neutral one."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.72,0:23:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它具有极小的质量 极少量的物质{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It has very little mass, a very small amount of matter...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.72,0:23:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}几乎没有 但它却具有能量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}almost nothing, but it has energy...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.89,0:23:21.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它穿越空间 速度几近光速{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and it zips through space at close to the speed of light.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.15,0:23:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这些东西是非互动性的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}These things are so non-interactive...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.78,0:23:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}要是你设想有一光年厚的铅{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that if you imagine a light-year thickness of lead...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.12,0:23:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你拿一束中微子射向它{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and you shined a beam of neutrinos toward it...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.75,0:23:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其中一半的中微子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}half of those neutrinos...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.00,0:23:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}将会穿过这一光年厚的铅{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}would make it through that light-year thickness of lead...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.75,0:23:47.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}居然毫发无伤{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}completely unscathed.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.84,0:23:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}中微子最常见是形成于{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Neutrinos are most commonly formed...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.80,0:23:57.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}恒星内部的核反应 包括我们的太阳{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}by nuclear reactions inside stars, including our Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.69,0:24:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}每秒钟约有600亿个太阳中微子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}About 60 billion solar neutrinos...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.20,0:24:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}穿过我们的拇指{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}pass through our thumbnails every second.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.91,0:24:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不过还有其它源头产生着中微子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But there are other sources that create neutrinos.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.13,0:24:27.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们产生于核反应堆{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They are produced by nuclear reactors...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.96,0:24:29.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有些产生于一直就在我们周围的岩石里的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there are some being produced by the radioactive decay...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.01,0:24:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}元素的放射性衰变{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of elements in the rock around us all the time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.93,0:24:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}还有实际上是产生于{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And there are others that are actually produced...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.47,0:24:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙射线轰击我们的大气层{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}when cosmic rays slam into our atmosphere.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.31,0:24:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们轰击大气层的力量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And they hit the atmosphere literally with the force...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.06,0:24:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}相当于时速100英里的快球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of a 100-mile-an-hour fastball.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.07,0:24:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}海量的中微子被释放进宇宙{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Vast numbers of neutrinos were released into the universe...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.40,0:24:58.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}紧接着大爆炸 伴随着其它粒子和光{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}immediately after the Big Bang, along with other particles and light.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.74,0:25:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}人类就是这种原生汤的后裔{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Humans are the descendants of this primordial soup.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.75,0:25:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}中微子是不同寻常的小不点{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Neutrinos are unusual small objects...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.17,0:25:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但是同样存在着不同凡响的大玩意{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but there are equally out of the ordinary big things.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.72,0:25:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}小行星就是太阳系形成时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Asteroids are the rocky leftovers...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.06,0:25:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所残留的石头{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}from the formation of the solar system.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.07,0:25:31.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这些太空石块主要呆在{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}These space rocks primarily orbit...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.03,0:25:34.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}火星与木星之间的小行星带里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}within the asteroid belt between Jupiter and Mars.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.28,0:25:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在定居小行星带里的数十亿个里头{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Among the billions that inhabit the asteroid belt...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.12,0:25:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有一个小行星真是模样古怪{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there's one asteroid that's truly eccentric.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.42,0:25:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}最怪异的小行星叫做图塔蒂斯{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}One of the strangest asteroids is one called Toutatis...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.34,0:25:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我想它之所以引人瞩目就在于它与众不同{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and l guess it catches our attention a lot because it's odd.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.26,0:25:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它不是球形的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's not perfectly round.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.30,0:25:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它有点畸形{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's kind of misshapen.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.43,0:26:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它看上去像是保龄球瓶 细长的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It sort of looks like a bowling pin, elongated...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.06,0:26:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}下面鼓起来 然后有个狭长的脖子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}like a bulge down here and then a narrow neck...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.27,0:26:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}然后一头又鼓起来{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and then another bulge.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.31,0:26:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有人甚至称{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Some have even said...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.35,0:26:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它有可能是两个单独的物体松散地结合在一起的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it's maybe two separate objects loosely connected.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.94,0:26:15.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它有一个奇怪的自转周期 好像在翻跟斗{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's got a strange rotational period where it's sort of tumbling...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.61,0:26:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就像是没投好的橄榄球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}kind of like a badly thrown football.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.07,0:26:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其旋转并没有任何主轴{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's not spinning along any of its primary axes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.24,0:26:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它实际上是沿着三个方向{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's actually sort of spinning along all three...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.66,0:26:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在太空中翻滚{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}tumbling through space.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.17,0:26:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}图塔蒂斯也有一个大椭圆轨道{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Toutatis also has a highly elliptical orbit...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.09,0:26:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}把它从小行星带里带到地球的轨道内{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which carries it from the asteroid belt to inside the Earth's orbit.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.51,0:26:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它是颗越地小行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's an Earth-Crossing asteroid...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.26,0:26:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}使它进入危险区{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and that puts it in the danger zone...{\r}
